<h1 class='property-title'>display</h1>
<p class='property-description'>The <code>display</code> CSS property specifies the type of rendering box used for an element. In HTML, default <code>display</code> property values are taken from behaviors described in the HTML specifications or from the browser/user default stylesheet. The default value in XML is <code>inline</code>.</p>